OL,4,G2230FBritish Art at War: Bomberg,
OL,5,     FSickert and Nash
OL,6,     GAndrew Graham-Dixon tells the
OL,7,     Gstory of David Bomberg, the
OL,8,     Gstartlingly original British
OL,9,     Gpainter who died in obscurity
OL,10,     Gover 50 years ago.
OL,11,G2330FArt That Made Us
OL,12,     GWith the industrial revolution
OL,13,     Gtransforming the British Isles,
OL,14,     Gthe cities and country are
OL,15,     Gdivided, and artists respond to
OL,16,     Gthe upheavals to lives and the
OL,17,     Glandscape.
